window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>In six hundred years, one thing hasn't changed . . .</b><br> <br> Crooked politicians still exist. But Gen Beaufont hasn't changed eitherâ€”she still fights for justice, no matter what.<br> <br> <b>Although Gen is from the medieval era, she understands the politics of the modern world.</b><br> <br> When the Rogue Riders become divided by their own principles, things really get dangerous. If those meant to protect are at odds with each other, is there any hope for the citizens they are meant to protect?<br> <br> <b>Not only must Gen and her dragon bring down corruption, but they must find a way to destroy the leader of the Rogue Riders.</b><br> <br> The medieval warrior suspected that Dwayne Stone was evil from the beginning, but she had no idea how much so . . .<br> <br> <b>Can Gen Beaufont expose the mastermind behind the corruption and save the state of California from the brink of chaos?</b> Or will the criminals lurking in the shadows take over, unleashing an evil so rampant that it could consume not just the state, but the entire world?</p>"; 
